solutions.content:
**Understanding the Problem:**

As per the problem, the robot starts at (0,0) facing north and we have to find if the robot is not going to leave the circle. 
Based on this assumption we can say - if after travelling some (x,y) distance, the robot continues to be in the north direction then the robot will leave the circle till which it has travelled till now. If it is in any other direction then we say it is going to be in the circle.

From this understanding we can deduce the following -
- If the robot is in (x, y) plane facing northward/upward and not in the starting position (0,0) then it is **not in a circle**
- In all other cases the robot is considered to be **in a circle**
	- Robot is in starting position (0, 0) pointing to any direction
	- Robot is in any position (x, y) other than starting, but facing in any of the directions - East, West, South, other than North.

**Code:**
```
class Solution {
    public boolean isRobotBounded(String instructions) {

        // Denotes the 'N', 'E', 'S', 'W' co-ordinates
        int dir[][] = {
            {0,1},  //North
            {1,0},  //East
            {0,-1}, //South
            {-1,0}  //West
        };

        // Co-ordinates in the dir[][] plane
        // dir[*][0] --> x
        // dir[*][1] --> y
        int x=0, y=0;

        // Index denoting the direction 
        // i = 0 --> North/Up
        // i = 1 --> East/Right
        // i = 2 --> South/Down
        // i = 3 --> West/Left
        int i=0; 

        for(char c : instructions.toCharArray()){
            if(c == 'L') 
                i = (i + 3) % 4;
            else if(c == 'R') 
                i = (i + 1) % 4;
            else {
                x += dir[i][0]; // Calculating the x distance
                y += dir[i][1]; // Calculating the y distance
            }
        }
        return x == 0 && y == 0 || i > 0;
    }
}
```

