### Theory
No tricks here, just simulate the robot movement. The robot is constraint if it ends back at the origin or if ends up elsewhere facing any direction but north.

### Solution
```
    public boolean isRobotBounded(String instructions) {
        DIRECTION dir = DIRECTION.NORTH;
        int[] pos = new int[] {0, 0};
        for (int i = 0; i < instructions.length(); i++) {
            Character c = instructions.charAt(i);
            if (c == 'G') move(dir, pos);
            else dir = turn(dir, c);
        }

        boolean atOrigin = pos[0] == 0 && pos[1] == 0;
        boolean facingNorth = dir == DIRECTION.NORTH;


        return atOrigin || !facingNorth;

    }

    private void move(DIRECTION dir, int[] pos) {
        if (dir == DIRECTION.NORTH) {
            pos[1]++;
