# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
We have to find if the robot in the end remains at any other position than origin(beginning point) and is in north direction, then by this we can conclude it will never be able to reach back at the same position with same direction.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
$$O(n)$$, where n is length of the string.

- Space complexity:
