solutions.content:
**Idea:**
* To change position (G), move one step along the current facing direction
* To turn left, `(X, Y) -> (-Y, X)`. [Read more here](https://math.stackexchange.com/questions/1330161/how-to-rotate-points-through-90-degree/1330166#1330166)
* To turn right, `(X, Y) -> (Y, -X)`
* At the end the robot is bounded if:
	* it returns to Origin (zero displacement), or
	* the facing direction has changed, which can happen with a change in either horizontal or vertical component of the direction
>**T/S:** O(n)/O(1), where n = size(instructions)
```
public boolean isRobotBounded(String instructions) {
	var x = 0; // horizontal position
	var y = 0; // vertical position
	var dirs = new int[]{0, 1}; // horizontal and vertical directions respectively, initially facing north

	for (var i = 0; i < instructions.length(); i++)
		switch (instructions.charAt(i)) {
			case 'G' -> {
				x += dirs[0];
				y += dirs[1];
			}
			case 'L' -> swap(dirs, true);
			case 'R' -> swap(dirs, false);
		}

	return x == 0 && y == 0 || dirs[0] != 0 || dirs[1] != 1;
}

private void swap(int[] dirs, boolean negativeY) {
	var temp = dirs[0];
	dirs[0] = negativeY ? -dirs[1] : dirs[1];
	dirs[1] = negativeY ? temp : -temp;
