**Explanation:**
Only if the robot returns to a **different position with the same facing direction** as the start point after the instructions, it will go infinitly away from the start point.
In all other cases, i.e.,

1. same position, same direction;
2. same position, different direction;
2. different position, different direction,

the robot with be bounded in a circle.
```
public boolean isRobotBounded(String instructions) {
    int x = 0, y = 0, direction = 0;
	// north: 0, east: 1, south: 2, west: 3;
    for (int i = 0; i < instructions.length(); i++) {
	    // update the direction
		char c = instructions.charAt(i);
	    if (c == 'L') direction = Math.floorMod(--direction, 4);
        if (c == 'R') direction = Math.floorMod(++direction, 4);
		if (c == 'G') {
		    // move the robot according to its direction 
	        if (direction == 0) y++;
            if (direction == 1) x++;
			if (direction == 2) y--;
            if (direction == 3) x--;
        }
    }
	// only if robot returns to a different position with the same facing direction
	// as the start point, return false
    if (direction == 0 && (x != 0 || y != 0)) return false;
	return true;
}
```
**Complexity:**
Time: O(N)
Space: O(1)

