# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
**Step 1: -** Standing on root node, we will calculate the number of occurences of each alphabet i.e. ```target``` in every possible subtree.
**Step 2: -** Store the count in ```hash```.
**Step 3: -** Return the count of the desired target i.e. ```hash[target]``` simultaneously updating the value of ```res[root_node] = hash[labels[root_node]-'a']```.

The above process is done for each node of the tree.

# Approach
The above Intuition will result in ```TLE``` because above intuition have a time complexity of ```26^(height of the tree)``` when tree is skewed tree.

*For complete tree it results in ```26^(height of the tree) * constant```. Here constant is sum of children of each node.*

So, in order to prevent repeated computations, we can store the result in a ```unordered_map<int, vector<int>> m``` and return the required target value without computing it again. 
Thus, making the time complexity ```O(N)```.

# Complexity
- Time complexity: ```O(N)```
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity: ```O(height of the tree + n + n*26)```
Here,
 n - adjacency list
      n*26 - unordered_map 
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    unordered_map<int, vector<int>> m;

    int helper (vector<int> *adj, string &labels, int vertex, int target, vector<int>&res, int parent){
        if (m.find (vertex) != m.end ()) return m[vertex][target]; //return cached result

        // Base condition
        if ((adj[vertex].size () == 1 && adj[vertex][0] == parent) || adj[vertex].size () == 0){
            res[vertex] = 1;

            if (target == (labels[vertex]-'a')) return 1;
            return 0;
        }

        vector<int> hash (26); // store coun of each alphabet

        //exploring each alphabet for every subtree
        for (int i = 0; i < 26; i++){
            int ans = 0;
            if (i == (labels[vertex]-'a')) ans++;

            for (auto x: adj[vertex]){
                if (parent != x)
                ans += helper (adj, labels, x, i, res, vertex);
            }

            hash[i] = ans;
        }

        m[vertex] = hash; // caching the result
        res[vertex] = hash[labels[vertex]-'a'];

        if (target == -1) return{};  // to prevent root element to give runtime error     
        return hash[target];

    }
    vector<int> countSubTrees(int n, vector<vector<int>>& edges, string labels) {
        vector<int> res (n); // for result
        vector<int> adj [n];

        for (int i = 0; i < edges.size (); i++){
            adj[edges[i][0]].push_back (edges[i][1]);
            adj[edges[i][1]].push_back (edges[i][0]);
        }


        helper (adj, labels, 0, -1, res, 0);

        return res;
    }
};
```

