# Approach
We simply traverse the tree top-down, incrementing each label counter whenever occured. Main idea is to remember label counter before we started traversing subtree and put the difference after it

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
$$O(n)$$
- Space complexity:
$$O(n)$$
# Code
```
func countSubTrees(n int, edges [][]int, labels string) []int {
    children := make([][]int, n)
    results := make([]int, n)
    for _, edge := range edges {
        i, j := edge[0], edge[1]
        children[i] = append(children[i], j)
        children[j] = append(children[j], i)
    }
    var counts [26]int
