# Explanation
    1) Build a generic tree(tree having 0 or more branches) using 
    hashmap to store the Node value as key and reference as value of 
    the map.
    2) Use dfs function to traverse through the tree with return type 
    vector:
        a) create a vector of letters (size:26)
        b) recursively call for the children nodes of the root.
        c) calculate sum of letter indices and return array indices
           for all 26 letters.
        d) Lastly increment the value of current label in the letter
           by 1. this would keep track of number of each label from 
           (a-z) in the present subtree.
    3) return letter array for each recursive call.
